{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = Charlie Wilson's War: The Extraordinary Story of the Largest Covert Operation in History | image = Charlie Wilson's War The Extraordinary Story of the Largest Covert Operation in History.jpg| image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = George Crile III | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | release_number = | subject = | genre = | set_in = | publisher = Atlantic Monthly Press | publisher2 = | pub_date = | english_pub_date = | published = | media_type = | pages = | awards = | isbn = 978-0871138545 | isbn_note = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = }} '''''Charlie Wilson's War: The Extraordinary Story of the Largest Covert Operation in History''''' (later titled '''''Charlie Wilson's War: The Extraordinary Story of How the Wildest Man in Congress and a Rogue CIA Agent Changed the History of Our Times''''') was a 2003 book by [[George Crile III]]. It detailed U.S. Representative [[Charlie Wilson (Texas politician)|Charlie Wilson]]'s role in providing assistance to the [[Mujahideen#Afghanistan|Afghan Mujahideen]] during the [[Soviet–Afghan War]].<ref name="NYTJohnston">{{cite news|last1=Johnston|first1=David|title=Wilson the Warrior|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/05/25/books/wilson-the-warrior.html|accessdate=June 4, 2017|work=The New York Times|date=May 25, 2003}}</ref> It was adapted into the 2007 [[Mike Nichols]] film ''[[Charlie Wilson's War (film)|Charlie Wilson's War]]'', in which Wilson was portrayed by [[Tom Hanks]].
